@NODE introduction "Introduction"

    Are you creating Web-sites and likes those little animations
    made from GIF-pictures?
    Or are you just making GIF-animations for fun?
    In any case. Are you using WhirlGIF and goes crazy over the
    commandline usage?

     This is the solution then. @{" MUI " link mui } is used to create a
    user-friendly Graphical User Interface (a window) to compose
    GIF-animations.

     Requirements:
        AmigaWorkbench 3.0
        MUI 3.8                          @{" Information " link mui }
        WhirlGIF 2.01                    @{" Information " link whirlgif }
        An animation-viewer (optionally) @{" Information " link bt_viewanim }
        A picture-viewer (optionally)    @{" Information " link bt_viewpic }

     Enough! Take a look at the @{" Usage " link usage } section now.

@ENDNODE

@NODE install "Installation"

      The installation of GIFComposer is as simple as it could be.
     Just start the program!
      As this is the beta (preview) release, I haven't implemented
     Locale-support or online-help or anything like that so
     installation is not needed. It will come later.

      @{B}BUT!@{UB}

      Because GIFComposer requires another program (WhirlGIF) to
     work, you'll have to get it first. Check @{"here" link whirlgif } for more info
     about WhirlGIF.
      GIFComposer maust know about where you have installed WhirlGIF
     so you'll have to type in the path to WhirlGIF in GIFComposers
     ToolTypes. Check your Workbench manual if you don't know how to
     edit ToolTypes.
     Look for a ToolType that says "WHIRLGIF=<path>". Replace <path>
     with the path where WhirlGIF is on your harddrive.

@ENDNODE


@NODE usage "Usage"

    @{b}How to use GIFComposer@{ub}

     @{" Quick tutorial " link tut }
     @{" Main window    " link window }


    @{b}Configuration@{ub}

     The configuration of GIFComposer is divided in three parts.
    ·@{" Program settings " link prefs_prog } is made in the tooltypes of GIFComposers icon.
    ·@{" Global animation settings " link prefs_anim } is made from within the program.
     Select the menuchoice "Preferences" to open the global-settings-window.
    ·@{" Individual picture settings " link prefs_picture } is not availiable in this version.

@ENDNODE

@NODE window "GIFComposer main window"

    This is the main window of GIFComposer. It consists of
    several parts and looks something like this(!?):

        @{"          Pictures in animation         " link lv_anim }
        @{"    Add     " link bt_add }@{"     Up     " link bt_up }@{"  Duplicate  " link bt_dup }
        @{"   Remove   " link bt_del }@{"    Down    " link bt_down }@{"   Options   " link bt_options }

        @{"             Output file                " link pop_output }

        @{"  Make Anim " link bt_makeanim }@{"  View Anim " link bt_viewanim }@{" View Picture " link bt_viewpic }

@ENDNODE

@NODE lv_anim "Pictures in animation"

     This is the main part of GIFComposers interface.
    The pictures in this list are the parts of your
    animation. You may add, delete and duplicate
    pictures as well as move them up and down with
    the buttons below the list.
     The selected picture may also be viewed vith a
    press on the @{" View Picture " link bt_viewpic } button.

@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_add "Add"

     Opens up a file-requester which lets you choose a
    GIF-picture. It will be added to the main list,
    @{" Pictures in anim " link lv_anim}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_up "Up"

     Moves the selected picture in the list up one step.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_dup "Duplicate"

     Copies the selected picture-name and places the
    copy below all the others in the list.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_del "Remove"

     Removes the selected picture-name.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_down "Down"

     Moves the selected picture in the list down one step.

@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_options "Options"

     -->NOT IMPLEMENTED YET<--
@ENDNODE

@NODE pop_output "Output file"

    Opens a filerequester and lets you choose the name
   your finished animation should have.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_makeanim "Make Anim"

     Creates the animation using the pictures in the list
    @{" Pictures in anim " link lv_anim}, in the same order they appear,
    and saves it as a GIF-animation file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_viewanim "View Anim"

     To use this feature, you must have an external viewer
    program that will show GIF-animations, XAnim is good
    for this purpose. You can find XAnim on Aminet.
    If you have got Workbench 3.1+, you could use Multiview
    to view animations (I haven't tried it yet).
     To configure GIFComposer for this, check the @{" Preferences " link prefs_prog }
    section of this documentation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE bt_viewpic "View Picture"

     Just like @{" view anim " link bt_viewanim }, this function uses an external
    viewer program. Use Multiview or similar picture viewer
    for this purpose.
     To configure GIFComposer for this, check the @{" Preferences " link prefs_prog }
    section of this documentation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE prefs_prog "Tooltype settings"

     Tooltypes used by GIFComposer.

    PATH=<drawer>
     This is the drawer where GIFComposer should start to look for
     pictures and other stuff when a filerequester is opened.

    VIEWPICTURE=<command>
     The command to execute when the button @{" View Picture " link bt_viewpic } is pressed.
     A pictureviewer should be started with the selected picture
     as argument. The argument (picture) is substituted with a
     %f. For example, if you are using Multiview:
        sys:utilities/multiview %f

    VIEWANIM=<command>
     Just like VIEWPICTURE but this command is executed when the
     button @{" View Animation " link bt_viewanim } is pressed.

    WHIRLGIF=<path>
     As GIFComposer uses @{" WhirlGIF " link whirlgif } to create the anim, you
     must tell GIFComposer where WhirlGIF is. If you put it in C: you
     should type "c:whirlgif" here.
@ENDNODE

@NODE prefs_anim "Animation settings"

    This section is not written yet.
@ENDNODE

@NODE prefs_picture "Picture settings"

     -->NOT IMPLEMENTED YET<--
@ENDNODE


@NODE tut "A little tutorial"

             @{b}How to compose a GIF animation@{ub}

     First of all you need some pictures. This program takes
    several GIF-pictures and merges them together so it looks
    like a moving picture. You should compose theese pictures
    in a suitable program like Deluxe Paint or similar which
    have animation support. This kind of program is only a
    help with the animation-part, you could use IconEdit or
    anything if you want to but it's harder.
     You could also use a 3d modelling program like Real3D or
    Imagine which also have the ability to create animations.

     NOTE! Save the stuff as different pictures and not as an
    IFF-animation.

     Theese pictures are then needed to be converted to GIF
    format or, if your paint-program supports it, save them
    as GIF's. (Personal Paint can save GIF-pictures but not
    Deluxe Paint.)

     Now when you have several GIF-pictures, you may start
    GIFComposer.
     First press the button labeled @{" Add " link bt_add }. A filerequester
    opens and asks you to choose the pictures you have created.
    Select them all and press OK. The names of the pictures
    will show up in the listview @{" Pictures in animation " link lv_anim }.
     Now you could edit the order they will be played in with
    the buttons "Up" and "Down". You may also delete them from
    the list and duplicate them if you want some to show many
    times.
     Next step is to name the created animation should have.
    Enter it in the "Output file" field or press the button
    rightmost of it and select a filename.
     You may set some options with the menuchoice @{" Preferences " link prefs_anim }
    or the button named @{" Options " link prefs_picture } if you want too.

     Now you are finished and all that is left is to create the
    anim. Simply press "Make Anim" and a progress window is opened.
    When the window says "Processed xx files" (or similar) your
    animation is finished.
     Press "View Anim" and enjoy. To view the animation, you
    need an external viewer. Read more about that in the
    @{" Tooltype section " link  prefs_prog } or in the section about the button
    @{" View Anim " link bt_viewanim }.


@ENDNODE

@NODE bugs "Bugs, limitations and future"

     No special bugs are implemented by the moment (okay there
    might be some but I don't know anything about it).

     Anyway, some things need to be done. If you add a picture,
    you'll see that the whole path to the picture is shown.
    Just imagine if you have some pics which lies in the drawer:
    Work:Programs/Grafix/Real3d/projects/pictures/vehicles/cars/chevys/camaro_67's_with_big_tires/
    You might see the names of the pictures if you enlarge the
    window and if you're very lucky, but I (personally) don't
    like it. (Who would?)
     Thats something that needs to be done. GIFComposer is still
    usable if your pics dont lies too deep in the caves of your
    harddrive. You could also make an assign or something.
    (Everything has a solution (except for the Amiga-buyout (or?).)


