@NODE whirlgif "About WhirlGIF"

     WhirlGIF is a PD-program made by Kevin Kadow (Amiga version by
    Lars Eilebrecht). It is a shell-based program, kinda hard to
    use, and that's the reason I made a GUI for it.
     It supports transparency, 4 different disposal methods,
    Netscape-looping and adjustable framerate.
     GIFComposer uses WhirlGIF 2.01 to create animations, all the
    options WhirlGIF uses are supported by GIFComposer.


    WhirlGIF is available from http://www.msg.net/utility/whirlgif/
    Author: Kevin Kadow   kadokev@msg.net

    Amiga version available from aminet/gfx/conv/
    Author: Lars SFX Eilebrecht   SFX@unix-ag.uni-siegen.de
    
    WhirlGIF is based on 'txtmerge' written by:
    Mark Podlipec   podlipec@wellfleet.com

@ENDNODE

@NODE usefulinfo "Some useful(or less) information"

    @{B}Animation viewing@{UB}

     If you are planning to view your animations from within
    GIFComposer, you have to get an animation-viewer.
    You can use IBrowse if you want to but it might not be
    so handy. The only program I know able to show GIF-
    animations is XAnim. It's availiable at Aminet in the
    directory gfx/show/.
     One problem with XAnim is that it needs a stack that is
    bigger than (or same as) 20000 bytes. It caused me some
    problems first but it is actually easy solved with the
    aid of a script file that sets the stack to 20000 and
    the executes XAnim. I have made a such file for those of
    you who are not shell-freaks. If you put this file and
    XAnim in the same directory as GIFComposer you'll just
    have to type "execute progdir:xxanim %f" in the field
    "View Animation Command" in the window "Program settings"
    and there you go! If you have XAnim somewhere else you'll
    have to edit the script to suit your needs.

     I know that Multiview cannot show GIF-animations although
    it can show IFF-anims (strange), that is with the standard
    animation.datatype and ZGIF-datatype, but someone might
    know better than me in this case (I might have missed some
    new GIF or animation datatypes). Contact me in that case or
    if you know anything about other programs able to show GIF-
    anims.


@ENDNODE

